<TITLE> Beckham to make Real Madrid squad to face Zaragoza </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, June 8 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - David Beckham will be included in the Real Madrid squad to play at Real Zaragoza on Saturday, after making good progress on an ankle injury, the Primera Liga leaders said on Friday. The LA Galaxy-bound Beckham injured his left ankle during England's 3-0 win over Estonia in a Euro 2008 qualifier on Wednesday, and was substituted midway through the second half. Although he trained apart from the rest of the team on Friday, the club said he would make the squad for the potential title decider in Zaragoza, on their Web site www.realmadrid.com Real top the Primera Liga with 72 points, ahead of Barcelona due to their superior head-to-head record, with two games left. Sevilla are two points behind in third place
